## Critical Implementation Details

### Timer Usage
{{TIMER_USAGE}}
<!--
Example:
- **Timer0**: System tick (Arduino millis/micros)
- **Timer1**: PWM generation for motor control
- **Timer2**: Reserved for audio synthesis
-->

### Interrupt Priorities
{{INTERRUPT_PRIORITIES}}
<!--
Example:
- **Highest**: Critical communication ISR
- **Medium**: Sensor data ready
- **Lowest**: User interface updates
-->

### Memory Optimization Guidelines
{{MEMORY_GUIDELINES}}
<!--
Example:
- Use PROGMEM for const data (Flash storage)
- Avoid deep recursion (limited stack)
- Use uint8_t/uint16_t instead of int where possible
- Minimize global variables
-->

### Power Management
{{POWER_MANAGEMENT}}
<!--
Example:
- Normal operation: {{NORMAL_CLOCK}} clock
- Low power mode: Sleep when idle, wake on interrupt
- Ultra-low power: Deep sleep with RTC wakeup
- Battery monitoring: ADC reading every 60 seconds
-->

