## Best Practices

### Code Style
- Follow {{CODE_STYLE}} (e.g., Google C++ Style, Arduino conventions)
- Use meaningful variable names
- Comment hardware interactions and timing-critical code
- Document ISR behavior and constraints

### Testing
- Unit tests in `test/` directory
- Hardware-in-loop testing for peripheral drivers
- Memory leak detection (valgrind for simulation)
- Timing verification with oscilloscope/logic analyzer

### Documentation
- Update HardwareDefinition.md for pin changes
- Document calibration procedures
- Keep design decisions in docs/Design_Summary.md
- Add TODO comments for known issues

